==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Melene
<hw>Mel"ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Mel</ets>issic +
ethyl<ets>ene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An unsaturated
hydrocarbon, <chform>C30H60</chform>, of the ethylene series, obtained
from beeswax as a white, scaly, crystalline wax; -- called also
<altname>melissene</altname>, and
<altname>melissylene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

